name: ethylphosphonic acid
Reason: The basic unit, phosphonic acid, has a melting point of 70.9°C. The ethyl group generally increases the molecular weight which can lead to an increase in the melting point, but it can also introduce more flexibility into the molecule, which can lower the melting point. In this case, because the ethyl group is relatively small and the molecule still benefits from the strong hydrogen bonds in the phosphonic acid, the net effect is likely a slight reduction in the melting point. Ethyl group: -10°C (flexibility and reduced compactness outweigh slight molecular weight increase resulting in a lower melting point).
